    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Units of illuminance measured as the degree of illumination that falls upon the interior of a sphere with a radius of one foot from a uniform point source of light of one candle and equal to one lumen per square foot. In the metric system, a lumen is measured by a square meter or a lux. Thus a foot-candle is equivalent to approximately 10 lux or 10.57 lux.</Note_Text>
